'''Mishima Shrine''' (みしまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Takashima, Shiga|Q845794|qid=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|qid=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is identified as the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} Mishima Shrine (みしまじんじゃ)<ref name=特選神名牒>[https://dl.ndl.go.jp/pid/971155/1/243 特選神名牒]</ref>.

Its records were lost in a fire, so the founding history is unknown<ref>『高島郡誌』141p</ref>. However, it is identified with Mishima Shrine of {{ill|lt=Takashima District, Shiga|Q11669692|qid=Q11669692|lt=Takashima District|1=Takashima District, Shiga}}, a Shikinaisha<ref name=特選神名牒/>, so it must have been founded before {{ill|lt=927|Q30470|qid=Q30470|1=927}}, when the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} was compiled.

Because "Mishima" (written 箕島) is a homophone of "Mishima" (三島), and it is commonly called Mishima Myōjin<ref name=特選神名牒/>, it is also regarded as related to {{ill|lt=Mishima and Ōyama cult|Q127948103|qid=Q127948103|1=Mishima–Ōyamazumi cult}} and assigned {{ill|qid=Q386563|lt=Ōyamatsumi|Q386563|qid=Q386563|qid=Q386563|lt=Ōyamatsumi-no-Kami|1=Ōyamatsumi}}. In other cases, the deity is also given as {{ill|qid=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi|Q8009611|qid=Q8009611|qid=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Kami|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto}} or {{ill|lt=Amatsu Kunitama no Mikoto|Q135271288|qid=Q135271288|1=Ama no Kantama no Mikoto}}.

=== Enshrined deity ===
; Principal enshrined deity
* {{ill|qid=Q386563|lt=Ōyamatsumi|Q386563|qid=Q386563|qid=Q386563|lt=Ōyamatsumi-no-Kami|1=Ōyamatsumi}} (according to the Shikinaisha investigation report, ''Shiga-ken Jinja-shi'', Shiga Prefectural Shrine Office, shrine registers, and ''Takashima-gunshi'')
; Auxiliary shrine
* Musubi Shrine

